<div class="panel-group" id="accordion">
    <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading">
            <h4 class="panel-title">
                <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse1" aria-expanded="true" style="background:#F5F5F5 !important"><font color="black" size="5">What can be found on Panama Nest Ontology?</font></a>
            </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapse1" class="panel-collapse collapse in" aria-expanded="true">
            <div class="panel-body">
                <font color="black" size="4">
                    The aviafauna of Panama includes a total of 987 species according to Bird Checklists of the World. Most of this species can be found all over America and even in other continents. As an small country, the number of species within Panama's territory is immense. <br />
                    This ontology will provide information about birds of different orders and families. The data handled by the ontology includes the taxonomic rank of the birds and other characteristics like size, habitat, and common name. <br /> <br />
                    You can search data about any bird or you can use other parameters like the family, or the gen. The ontology will show the result according to the information you have searched. You can also expand the ontology by creating new elements.
                </font>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
  
    <div class="panel panel-default">
        <div class="panel-heading">
            <h4 class="panel-title">
                <a data-toggle="collapse" data-parent="#accordion" href="#collapse2" class="collapsed" aria-expanded="false" style="background:#F5F5F5 !important"><font color="black" size="5">Why choose an ontology?</font></a>
            </h4>
        </div>
        <div id="collapse2" class="panel-collapse collapse" aria-expanded="false">
            <div class="panel-body">
                <font color="black" size="4">
                    In order to maintain structured information on a web application you can use Semantic Web.
                    This can be defined as an extension of the Worldwide Web that contains information with explicit meaning  making it easier for machines to automatically process and integrate information available on the Web.
                    <br /> <br /> Semantic Web make use of many tools as vocabularies and ontologies to fullfill this goal. Ontologies
                    allow users to clasify content (like a taxonomy) which allows you to relate data based on the information in it as opposed to a term describing it. <br />
                    <br />This represents great value for organizatios because it allows to:

                    <ul>
                        <br />
                        <li>Manage content more effectively.</li>
                        <li>Maximize findability and discoverability of information.</li>
                        <li>Increase the reuse of “hidden” and unknown information.</li>
                        <li>Elevate SEO on external search engines.</li>
                    </ul>
                </font>
            </div>
        </div>
        </div>
